&nbsp;
The Egyptian Aviation Minister had ordered "that all facilities were prepared to welcome the corpse of the deceased", while the airport authorities of Aswan had adopted "all the necessary measures to ensure a warm welcome and organization of the arrival and departure of delegations who participated in funeral ceremonies". The Egyptian media reported that Aga Khan IV had expressed the desire to be buried in Aswan > because of the close ties that unite his family to this province of southern Egypt, in particular to the history of his grandfather, Aga Khan III suffering from rheumatism and to which for this reason the doctors had advised to care in the hot sands of Aswan.
&nbsp;
After resuming, the grandfather decided to build a mausoleum in the fatimide > style on a high hill in the province, to be buried there. On Saturday in Lisbon, a private funeral was held for about 300 people, attended by several prominent personalities, including the emeritus king of Spain Juan Carlos I and Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau. Rahim Aga Khan V, second of four children, became the 50th spiritual leader of the ismailites and will be the new imam of this Shiite creed, which is estimated to be accounts between 12 and 15 million followers in the world, distributed in 35 countries.

