AGI - Several US media - including Cnn - Russians - Interfax - and Ukrainians - Ukrainska Pravda - report of a phone call between President Donald Trump> and his Russian counterpart Vladimir Putin> to negotiate the end of the war. It was announced by Trump himself in an exclusive interview with the New York Post on board the Air Force One on Friday. In the interview, Trump said he believed Putin "would worry" about the dead on the battlefield. "He [Putin] wants to see people stop dying.> All those dead people. Young people, young people, beautiful people. They are like your children, two million of them, and no reason," Trump said.
&nbsp;
Trump then said that this war lasted for almost three years "would never happen" if he had been president in 2022, stating that "I always had a good relationship with Putin". Compared to his predecessor, Joe Biden, Trump commented that "Biden was an embarrassment for our nation. A complete embarrassment." The owner of the White House then made sure he had a specific plan to end the war. "I hope it's fast. People die every day. This war is so bad in Ukraine. I want to end this damn thing," Trump said at the New York Post. However, he didn't answer the interviewer's question that asked him how many times he'd already spoken to Putin in the last period, saying "better not to say that."
&nbsp;
<div </div
<br> "Let's start these meetings. They want to meet," Trump said, addressing national security advisor Mike Waltz, who was on board the Air Force One with him.
Trump also said he wanted to get a $500 million deal with President Volodymyr Zelensky for access to rare land minerals and Ukrainian gas in exchange for security guarantees in a potential peace agreement. On February 5, Putin's spokesman, Dmitry Peskov, recognized for the first time that there are contacts with President Trump's administration. In the past hours, Trump also said he could meet Zelensky next week. The Ukrainian president believes that his meeting with Trump should take place before determining the format of talks with Russia.&nbsp;&nbsp;
